    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Isaiah",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 1,
        "summary": "The people of Israel are apostate, rebellious, and corrupt; only a few remain faithful\u2014The people's sacrifices and feasts are rejected\u2014They are called upon to repent and work righteousness\u2014Zion will be redeemed in the day of restoration.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The vision of Isaiah the son of Amoz, which he saw concerning Judah and Jerusalem in the days of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of Judah.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Vision.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 19:23 (23\u201324); 3\u00a0Ne. 23:1.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Judah, People of.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 15:13 (1\u201313); Hosea 1:1.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 103
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 15:30, 38 (13\u201338); Micah 1:1.",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 111
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 16:20 (19\u201320).",
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 117
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 119,
                        "end": 122
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Hear, O heavens, and give ear, O earth: for the Lord hath spoken, I have nourished and brought up children, and they have rebelled against me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 32:1; D&C 1:1 (1\u20132); 76:1.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 32:19.",
                        "start": 122,
                        "end": 130
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The ox knoweth his owner, and the ass his master's crib: but Israel doth not know, my people doth not consider.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0stall or manger.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of Israel; God, Knowledge about; Ignorance.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ah sinful nation, a people laden with iniquity, a seed of evildoers, children that are corrupters: they have forsaken the Lord, they have provoked the Holy One of Israel unto anger, they are gone away backward.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Man, Natural, Not Spiritually Reborn.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 57:4.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 38:11 (10\u201312).",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 97
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Anger.",
                        "start": 175,
                        "end": 180
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Why should ye be stricken any more? ye will revolt more and more: the whole head is sick, and the whole heart faint.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0smitten.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Rebellion.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0diseased.",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 115
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "From the sole of the foot even unto the head there is no soundness in it; but wounds, and bruises, and putrifying sores: they have not been closed, neither bound up, neither mollified with ointment.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0squeezed out.",
                        "start": 140,
                        "end": 146
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0softened.",
                        "start": 174,
                        "end": 183
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 53
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Your country is desolate, your cities are burned with fire: your land, strangers devour it in your presence, and it is desolate, as overthrown by strangers.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 28:51 (51\u201352).",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 9:11; Micah 3:12; 2\u00a0Ne. 13:8.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Scattering of.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 118
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the daughter of Zion is left as a cottage in a vineyard, as a lodge in a garden of cucumbers, as a besieged city.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Vineyard of the Lord.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0a watchman's hut.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Except the Lord of hosts had left unto us a very small remnant, we should have been as Sodom, and we should have been like unto Gomorrah.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Remnant of.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Hear the word of the Lord, ye rulers of Sodom; give ear unto the law of our God, ye people of Gomorrah.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 16:46 (44\u201355).",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To what purpose is the multitude of your sacrifices unto me? saith the Lord: I am full of the burnt offerings of rams, and the fat of fed beasts; and I delight not in the blood of bullocks, or of lambs, or of he goats.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 15:22.",
                        "start": 152,
                        "end": 159
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "When ye come to appear before me, who hath required this at your hand, to tread my courts?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Bring no more vain oblations; incense is an abomination unto me; the new moons and sabbaths, the calling of assemblies, I cannot away with; it is iniquity, even the solemn meeting.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hypocrisy.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Chr. 23:31 (28\u201332).",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lam. 2:6.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 91
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 15:9.",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 118
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0endure. Ps. 101:5.",
                        "start": 129,
                        "end": 138
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 29:13.",
                        "start": 146,
                        "end": 154
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Solemn Assembly.",
                        "start": 165,
                        "end": 179
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 140,
                        "end": 145
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Your new moons and your appointed feasts my soul hateth: they are a trouble unto me; I am weary to bear them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 2:11.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 5:21.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 43:24 (24\u201328).",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 109
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And when ye spread forth your hands, I will hide mine eyes from you: yea, when ye make many prayers, I will not hear: your hands are full of blood.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 8:18; D&C 101:7 (7\u20138). TG\u00a0God, Access to.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 99
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0bloods; i.e., bloodshed. Isa. 59:2 (2\u20133).",
                        "start": 141,
                        "end": 146
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wash you, make you clean; put away the evil of your doings from before mine eyes; cease to do evil;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 7:3 (1\u20137). TG\u00a0Baptism.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Cleanliness; Purification; Purity.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Evil.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Repent.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Learn to do well; seek judgment, relieve the oppressed, judge the fatherless, plead for the widow.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Learn.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Good Works.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0justice.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Charity.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0give a just verdict to the fatherless.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 76
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Widows.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Come now, and let us reason together, saith the Lord: though your sins be as scarlet, they shall be as white as snow; though they be red like crimson, they shall be as wool.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 50:10.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forgive; Sin.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Purification.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 108
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "If ye be willing and obedient, ye shall eat the good of the land:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Teachable.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Obedience.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Abundant Life.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But if ye refuse and rebel, ye shall be devoured with the sword: for the mouth of the Lord hath spoken it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Rebellion.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Punish.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "How is the faithful city become an harlot! it was full of judgment; righteousness lodged in it; but now murderers.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of Israel.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0justice.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thy silver is become dross, thy wine mixed with water:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of Israel.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thy princes are rebellious, and companions of thieves: every one loveth gifts, and followeth after rewards: they judge not the fatherless, neither doth the cause of the widow come unto them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Kings, Earthly.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0bribes. Ezek. 22:12. TG\u00a0Bribe.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0\u201cdo not do justice to.\u201d TG\u00a0Judgment.",
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 122
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 863
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore saith the Lord, the Lord of hosts, the mighty One of Israel, Ah, I will ease me of mine adversaries, and avenge me of mine enemies:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 101:58.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 109
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will turn my hand upon thee, and purely purge away thy dross, and take away all thy tin:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0return; i.e., repeatedly chastise.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 9:7; Mal. 3:3.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will restore thy judges as at the first, and thy counsellors as at the beginning: afterward thou shalt be called, The city of righteousness, the faithful city.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 33:7 (7\u20138).",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Counselor.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jerusalem.",
                        "start": 124,
                        "end": 145
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Zion shall be redeemed with judgment, and her converts with righteousness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Zion.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0justice.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Conversion.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the destruction of the transgressors and of the sinners shall be together, and they that forsake the Lord shall be consumed.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For they shall be ashamed of the oaks which ye have desired, and ye shall be confounded for the gardens that ye have chosen.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0terebinth trees and gardens used in idol worship.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For ye shall be as an oak whose leaf fadeth, and as a garden that hath no water.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the strong shall be as tow, and the maker of it as a spark, and they shall both burn together, and none shall quench them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0as a tuft of inflammable fibers.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 9:16 (16\u201321).",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 126
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}